# Web: Lib Conventions

Conventions for code under `web/src/lib/`. Apply both when writing new lib code and when editing existing modules. Section **5** (Zod schema placement) and section **6** (`data` on pages) also apply to SvelteKit `+page.svelte` / `+layout.svelte` under `web/src/routes/` (and related `+page.server.ts` load validation).

---

## 1. Use $lib Paths for Imports

Import from `$lib` using the **alias path**, not relative paths (`./` or `../`) when the target is under `src/lib`.

- **Use**: `$lib/...` for any import whose target is under `web/src/lib/`.
- **Avoid**: Relative paths like `./file.svelte`, `../other.ts`, `./index.js` when those files are inside `src/lib`.
- **SvelteKit store import**: Prefer `import { page } from "$app/state";` and **avoid** `import { page } from "$app/stores";`.
- **Type-only imports**: Prefer `import type { ... }` when you only use types/interfaces and no runtime value is referenced, and still import them via `$lib/...` (never via `./` or `../`).

**Examples**

```svelte
<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
import DialogPortal from "$lib/ui/dialog/dialog-portal.svelte";
import { cn, type WithoutChildrenOrChild } from "$lib/ui/helpers/common";
import * as Dialog from "$lib/ui/dialog/index.js";

<!-- ❌ BAD -->
import DialogPortal from "./dialog-portal.svelte";
import { cn } from "../helpers/common";
import * as Dialog from "./index.js";
```

External packages are unchanged: use package names (e.g. `"bits-ui"`, `"svelte"`).

